The Kano State Government says it has recorded four additional cases of the COVID-19, making a total of 77 confirmed cases in the state.The state’s Ministry of Health made this known on its verified Twitter handle @KNSMOH. “Update as at 12:30 a.m. April 26, 2020; four new COVID-19 cases confirmed. “Total confirmed cases in Kano State are now 77, one COVID-19 death was recorded,” it said. It enjoined residents of the state to stay-at-home to break the chain of the virus transmission. Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. Produces when not on Social media.